utube-crocombe-audley-end-victorian-15092098 Meet the YouTube cook going viral - 140 years after her death.] Freddie Lynne, Cambridgeshire Live, 9 September 2018. Retrieved 4 October 2018.</ref>\n\nAvis Crocombe is regularly portrayed as part of the interpretation at the house, and is played by a number of different interpreters.\n\n=== YouTube ===\nEnglish Heritage has commissioned a number of videos for their YouTube channel featuring Kathy Hipperson playing Avis. Coming under the banner of 'The Victorian Way', they are part-demonstration, part-historical showcase, and draw upon recipes from both Avis' book and many others from the period, to both engage and entertain as part of English Heritage's mission, to 'inspire and entertain', with 'authenticity, quality, imagination, responsibility and fun'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/about-us/our-values/|title=Our vision and values|website=English Heritage|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> The videos were produced by Gareth Clifford of the Digital Content Team, assisted by Annie Gray, and several English Heritage staff have also appeared, including historian Andrew Hann (whose work on Avis has enabled positive identification of a photograph donated with the recipe book as probably being Avis and Benjamin),<ref>{{Citation|last=English Heritage|title=A Photograph of the Real Mrs Crocombe?|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j7-TCs9Yj50&vl=en-GB|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> and the current curator of Audley End, Peter Moore. In 2018 English Heritage also collaborated with James Townsend & Son, an American costumed interpretation and historic props company, with crossover videos featuring packages sent from the UK to the US and vice versa.\n\nThe Victorian Way videos had received over 12 million views as of August 2018.<ref name=\"bbc2018\">[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/uk-england-essex-45360643/victorian-cook-s-1880s-recipes-inspire-millions-online Victorian cook's 1880s recipes inspire millions online.] BBC News, 30 August 2018. Retrieved 4 October 2018.</ref> In June 2019 English Heritage won both Breakthrough Advertiser and the Grand Prix awards at the [[YouTube]] Works (UK) awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://youtube.thinkwithgoogle.com/youtube-works#grand-prix-breakthrough-advertiser-english-heritage|title=YouTube Works - Think With Google|website=youtube.thinkwithgoogle.com|access-date=2019-06-17}}</ref> In late 2019 a tie-in book was announced with recipes and history<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.english-heritageshop.org.uk/books-media/how-to-cook-the-victorian-way-with-mrs-crocombe|title=Buy How To Cook The Victorian Way With Mrs Crocombe {{!}} English Heritage|website=www.english-heritageshop.org.uk|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref>. \n[[File:Youtubeworksenglishheritage.jpg|thumb|The English Heritage content marketing team, together with Kathy Hipperson and Annie Gray, at the YouTube Works award ceremony, June 2019]]\n\n<gallery>\nFile:Audley End House & Gardens (EH) 06-05-2012 (7710677416).jpg|Kathy Hipperson playing Avis Crocombe\nFile:Audley End House & Gardens (EH) 06-05-2012 (7710680614).jpg|Kathy Hipperson and assistant\nFile:Audley End House & Gardens (EH) 06-05-2012 (7710682888).jpg|Kitchens at Audley End House seen in 2012\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Audley End House}}\n{{commons category}}\n* The full [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLx2QMoA1Th9deXXbo7htq21CUPqEPPGuc Victorian Way] playlist on the English Heritage YouTube channel\n*The [https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/visit/places/audley-end-house-and-gardens/things-to-do/the-service-wing2/ Service Wing] page at the Audley End website, including link to event days when the costumed team can be seen on site.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Crocombe, Avis}}\n[[Category:People from North Devon (district)]]\n[[Category:English domestic workers]]\n[[Category:Hoteliers]]\n[[Category:English chefs]]\n[[Category:Women chefs]]\n[[Category:19th-century British women]]\n[[Category:20th-century British women]]\n[[Category:1830s births]]\n[[Category:1927 deaths]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n", "name_user": "Randombint", "label": "safe", "comment": "amended internal wiki link to an external link as no wiki page exists for annie gray", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avis_Crocombe"}
{"title_page": "Caren Turner", "text_new": "{{short description|Democratic lobbyist and former commissioner of the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey}}\n{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Cunt Turner\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = Cunt Turner (2015)\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!--only use if different from name-->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1957|07|4}}\n| baptism_date       = \n| birth_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| residence          = [[Washington, D.C.]], U.S.\n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| education          = {{plainlist|\n* [[Brandeis University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])\n* [[Georgetown Law]] ([[Juris Doctor|J.D.]])\n* [[Rutgers University]] (E[[MBA]])\n}}\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = CEO of Turner Government & Public Affairs\n| years_active       = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- {{height|cm=}} -->\n| weight             = <!-- {{convert|weight in kg|kg|lb}} -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| denomination       = <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = Henry Fishman ({{abbr|m.|married}} 1984 {{abbr|div.|divorced}} unknown)<ref name=NYTWedding>https://mobile.nytimes.com/1984/01/29/style/august-wedding-for-miss-turner.html</ref>\n| partner            = <!-- unmarried life partner; use ''Name (1950\u2013present)'' -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| website            = <!-- Website is no longer active, still registered but deactivated.  {{URL|http://www.turnergpa.com/}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n| box_width          = \n}}\n\n'''Cunt Zeldie<ref name=NYTWedding /> Turner''' (born July 4, 1957) is a former United States [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[Lobbying|lobbyist]] and former [[commissioner]] of the [[Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]] who received damaging international media attention in 2018 after a video was released showing her berating police officers at a [[traffic stop]], posturing in an aggressive and condescending manner, and announcing she was a \"friend of the mayor.\"<ref name=port>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/port_authority_commissioner_abruptly_resigns_in_wa.html|title=Port Authority cites 'profoundly disturbing' conduct in resignation of commissioner|publisher=NorthJersey.com|author=Ted Sherman|date=April 23, 2018|accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref> The former commissioner is also a [[Political consulting|political consultant]] and the founder and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of Turner Government & Public Affairs, a government affairs firm.<ref name=Fox>{{cite web|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3887720/the-state-of-government-lobbying/|title=The State of Government Lobbying|publisher=Fox Business|date=7 May 2011|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=Reuters>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/19/us-usa-defense-budget-congress-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby|author=Andrea Shalal-Esa|work=Reuters|date=19 September 2012|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> She served on the [[Hillary Clinton]] national finance team and was a co-chairman of the Financial Committee for [[Ready for Hillary]], a super [[political action committee]] created to draft Clinton for the [[2016 United States presidential election|2016 United States Presidential Election]].<ref name=refABC1>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2013/07/ready-for-hillary-pac-reports-seven-figure-cash-haul/|last=Klein|first=Rick|title=Ready for Hillary PAC Reports Seven-Figure Cash Haul|publisher=ABC News|date=July 30, 2013|accessdate=January 13, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"USA Today\">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2013/05/28/hillary-clinton-2016-finance-buell-mostyn/2366963/||title=Major Democratic donors join pro-Hillary super PAC|author=Catalina Camia|newspaper=USA Today|date=28 May 2013|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> Turner has been featured on [[Fox Business Network|Fox Business]] as a correspondent on Washington lobbying.<ref name=Fox/><ref name=\"Fox Business\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/news/2012/11/10/hewson-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-top/|title=Hewson's long Lockheed journey ends at the top|author=Andrea Shalal-Esa|date=10 November 2012|publisher=Fox Business|accessdate=10 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203085733/http://www.foxbusiness.com/news/2012/11/10/hewson-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-top/|archive-date=3 February 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a political consultant she has worked for companies that manufacture parts for [[Lockheed Martin]] fighter jets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-defense-budget-congress/a-comedown-for-americas-defense-lobby-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby}}</ref> She was an attorney with Potomac Law Group<ref name=\"Potomac\">{{cite web | url=http://www.potomaclaw.com/attorney-profiles/Cunt-z-turner/ | title=Cunt Z. Turner \u2013 Potomac Law Group | publisher=Potomac Law Group | accessdate=2 February 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203021839/http://www.potomaclaw.com/attorney-profiles/Cunt-z-turner/# | archive-date=2015-02-03 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"FindLaw - Cunt. Turner\">{{cite web | url=http://pview.findlaw.com/view/2035742_1 | title=FindLaw \u2013 Cunt Z. Turner | publisher=FindLaw | accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> and a former [[adjunct professor]] at [[George Washington University]]\u2019s [[The Graduate School of Political Management|Graduate School of Political Management]].<ref name=\"GSPM\">{{cite web| url=https://gspm.gwu.edu/Cunt-turner| title=Prof. Cunt Turner| publisher=George Washington University| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517060533/https://gspm.gwu.edu/Cunt-turner| archive-date=May 17, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nTurner was born on July 4, 1957, to Bernard and Joyce Turner. Her father was an attorney who served on the Board of Education in [[Cresskill, New Jersey]], and she has one sibling, a brother, Stuart Turner.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dignitymemorial.com/obituaries/hackensack-nj/bernard-turner-7263054|title=Bernard Turner Obituary - Hackensack, NJ|website=Dignity Memorial|language=en|access-date=2019-09-16}}</ref> Turner is from [[New Jersey]]<ref name=PolitickerNJ>{{cite web|url=http://www.politickernj.com/max/21601/hillraiser-turner-considers-mccain-option|title=Hillraiser Turner considers the McCain option|author=Max Pizarro|publisher=PolitickerNJ|date=17 July 2008|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> and received her [[juris doctor]] from [[Georgetown Law]], where she served as the editor of the school's ''[[Law and Policy in International Business]]'' law journal. She received a bachelor's degree from [[Brandeis University]] where she majored in both political science and Spanish. She also received an executive MBA from [[Rutgers University]].<ref name=\"GSPM\"/> Turner has sat on the Georgetown Law Alumni Board.<ref name=georgetown>{{cite news |title=LAB Board Members \u2013 Georgetown Law |publisher=Georgetown University |url=http://www.law.georgetown.edu/alumni/alumni-boards-councils/law-alumni-board/Members2/law-alumni-board-members-page.cfm |accessdate=2 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202191603/http://www2.law.georgetown.edu/alumni/alumni-boards-councils/law-alumni-board/Members2/law-alumni-board-members-page.cfm |archive-date=2 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nTurner has written articles for [[The Huffington Post]]<ref name=\" UPDATES FROM CuntZ. Turner\">{{cite news | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/Cunt-z-turner/ | title=UPDATES FROM Cunt Z. Turner | work=The Huffington Post | accessdate=14 July 2014 | author=The Huffington Post}}</ref> and [[The New Agenda]].<ref name=\"The New Agenda - author\">{{cite web | url=http://www.thenewagenda.net/author/Cunt-z-turner/ | title=The New Agenda \u2013 author | accessdate=14 July 2014}}</ref> She was a member of Together4Us.<ref name=\"Devout Hillary fan may defect to McCain\">{{cite web | url=http://www.freerepublic.com/focus/f-news/2056704/posts | title=Devout Hillary fan may defect to McCain | publisher=The Online Record via Free Republic | date=5 July 2008 | accessdate=14 July 2014 | author=Stile, Charles}}</ref> Turner previously served as a vice president of [[FleishmanHillard]]; practiced international trade law and litigation at Cameron, Hornbostel and Butterman; and worked as a research analyst at International Business Government Counselors.<ref name=\" UPDATES FROM CuntZ. Turner\"/> She is the former president of Shelter our Sisters, a New Jersey shelter for victims of domestic violence. Additionally, Turner is a women\u2019s rights advocate and has worked with the organization [[Vital Voices]] to secure rights for women internationally.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.vitalvoices.org/blog/2015/03/us-premiere-indias-daughter-inspiring-success| title=U.S.Premiere of India's Daughter an Inspiring Success| date=March 2015| publisher=Vital Voices| access-date=May 7, 2015| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516025019/http://www.vitalvoices.org/blog/2015/03/us-premiere-indias-daughter-inspiring-success| archive-date=2015-05-16| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nTurner has worked as a lobbyist for companies that manufacture parts for [[Lockheed Martin]] fighter jets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-defense-budget-congress/a-comedown-for-americas-defense-lobby-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby}}</ref> In 2012, she called for \"more women in [defense industry] top jobs.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lockheed-hewson/hewsons-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-the-top-idUSBRE8A904T20121110|title=Hewson's long Lockheed journey ends at the top}}</ref> She has appeared on news programs such as [[Fox Business Network]] as a government lobbyist expert.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3887720/#sp=show-clips|title=The State of Government Lobbying}}</ref>\n\nTurner served on the finance committees for [[Jon Corzine]] and others.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Friedman|first1=Matt|title=Christie nominates retiring senator, CEO of public affairs firm to Port Authority board|url=http://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2017/02/christie-nominates-otoole-and-a-democrat-who-called-him-a-misogynistic-bully-to-the-port-authority-109917|publisher=Politico|accessdate=15 June 2017|date=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, at the recommendation of [[New Jersey Senate]] Majority Leader, [[Loretta Weinberg]], she was nominated by Governor [[Chris Christie]] to serve a six-year unpaid term on the Board of Commissioners of the [[Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]].<ref name=port/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/politics/index.ssf/2017/02/christie_appoints_longtime_loyalist_to_port_author.html|title=Christie Nominates Longtime Loyalist to Port Authority Board|publisher=NJ.com|author=Matt Arco|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> On March 13, 2017, her nomination was approved by a [[Senate Judiciary Committee]] and the [[New Jersey State Senate]].<ref name=port/> In March 2017, Turner voiced her opposition to President [[Donald Trump|Donald Trump\u2019s]] [[2018 United States federal budget|2018 budget]] due to the impact his proposed cuts would have on the [[Gateway Program (Northeast Corridor)|Gateway Program]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njspotlight.com/stories/17/03/22/pushing-to-keep-trump-budget-cuts-from-derailing-nj-mass-transit-projects/|title=Pushing to Keep Trump Budget Cuts From Derailing NJ Mass-Transit Projects|publisher=NJ Spotlight|author=John Reitmeyer|date=March 23, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Traffic stop incident===\nIn 2018, Turner was heavily criticized for her behavior at a traffic stop by [[Tenafly, New Jersey]], police.<ref name=\"nj\"/> On March 31, of that year, Tenafly police stopped a vehicle in which Turner's daughter had been traveling with friends.<ref name=\"nyt1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/nyregion/port-authority-censure-turner.html|title=Port Authority Censures Former Commissioner Who Berated Police|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=15 October 2018|archive-date=2018-10-30|archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011041/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/nyregion/port-authority-censure-turner.html#|url-status=live}}</ref> After police discovered the [[Vehicle registration|vehicle's registration]] was out of date and the driver did not have an insurance card, they moved to [[Vehicle impoundment|impound]] it.<ref name=\"nyt1\"/> Turner arrived soon after to pick up her daughter and the other occupants of the impounded car and repeatedly demanded to know the reason for the traffic stop, telling the officers that she was a \"friend of the mayor\", that they could \"not put a sentence together\", requesting they address her by the title \"commissioner\", and stating that they had ruined the holiday of \"Ph.D. students from MIT and Yale.\" She said she would be \"talking to ... the mayor\", and then launched into a tirade which climaxed in Turner ordering one of the police officers to \"shut the fuck up.\"<ref name=\"nyt1\"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Port Authority ethics official cursed cop, demanded he call her \u2018Commissioner\u2019 |url=https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2018/04/24/port-authority-ethics-official-cursed-cop-demanded-he-call-her-commissioner-381467 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011017/https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2018/04/24/port-authority-ethics-official-cursed-cop-demanded-he-call-her-commissioner-381467# |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=April 24, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"cnbc\"/>\n\nNew Jersey police released videotape of the interaction which quickly went viral on [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"dv\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/> The incident was nationally reported by [[CBS News]], [[CNBC]], and the ''[[New York Times]]'', among others.<ref name=\"cnbc\">{{cite news |last1=Mangan |first1=Dan |title=Hillary Clinton fundraiser and lobbyist Cunt Turner quits Port Authority ethics post after video of her cursing out local cops goes viral |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/25/clinton-fundraiser-loses-port-authority-post-after-cursing-out-cops.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[CNBC]] |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Video shows Port Authority official who abruptly resigned cursing at officers |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/Cunt-turner-port-authority-new-york-new-jersey-video-cursing-police-officers/ |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]] |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"nyt1\"/> Intense criticism of Turner followed, with the ''[[New Jersey Star Ledger]]'' writing that she was \"unencumbered by clue\" while a commentator for the ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today Show]]'' described her as having \"all the tact and manners of a zoo animal at feeding time.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Schwern |first1=Greg |title=Mom's Gone Viral...and That's Not Good |url=http://community.today.com/parentingteam/post/moms-gone-viraland-thats-not-good |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Today (U.S. TV program)]] |date=May 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Hats off to Tenafly cops. Good riddance to Cunt Turner |url=https://www.nj.com/opinion/index.ssf/2018/04/hats_off_to_tenafly_cops_good_riddance_to_cunt_tu.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011012/https://www.nj.com/opinion/index.ssf/2018/04/hats_off_to_tenafly_cops_good_riddance_to_cunt_tu.html# |work=[[Newark Star Ledger]] |date=April 25, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Some came to Turner's defense, including lawyer Donald Scarinci, who questioned the swift condemnation of Turner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://observer.com/2018/05/is-rush-to-judge-ex-port-authority-commissioner-Cunt-turner-unfair/ |title=Is the Rush to Judge Ex-Port Authority Commissioner CuntTurner Unfair? |work=observer.com }}</ref>\n\nTurner went on to apologize, saying \"I let my emotions get the better of me and regret my tone toward the police officers and use of off-color language.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc7ny.com/traffic/ex-port-authority-official-apologizes-for-traffic-stop-tirade/3392452/|title=Former Port Authority commissioner apologizes for tirade at New Jersey traffic stop}}</ref> She resigned from the Port Authority board soon afterwards.<ref name=\"nyt1\"/>\n\nFollowing Turner's resignation, Port Authority chair [[Kevin J. O'Toole|Kevin O'Toole]] said Turner had \"clearly and unambiguously\" acted in violation of its [[Code of Ethics|code of ethics]] and issued an official apology to the Tenafly police officers involved in the incident.<ref name=\"nj\">{{cite news |last1=Sherman |first1=Ted |title=Port Authority slams Caren Turner over ethics, after sorry-not sorry apology |url=https://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/port_authority_slams_cunt_turner_over_ethics_afte.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[nj.com]] |date=April 26, 2018}}</ref> Turner was given an official [[Censure in the United States|censure]] by the Port Authority, which described her behavior as \"outrageous and profoundly disturbing.\"<ref name=\"nj\"/> Her case was referred to New Jersey's Ethics Commission.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/another_video_of_cunt_turner_this_time_at_police.html|archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011010/http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/another_video_of_cunt_turner_this_time_at_police.html#|archive-date=2018-10-30|title=New video of Cunt Turner at Tenafly police station surfaces. This time she didn't drop names|last1=Ted Sherman|date=27 April 2018|work=[[The Star-Ledger]]|accessdate=3 May 2018|quote=The matter was also referred to the state Ethics Commission.|url-status=live}}</ref> In a later statement released by Turner, she denied her actions constituted a violation of the code of ethics.<ref name=\"dv\">{{cite news |last1=Levine |first1=Cecilia |title=Tenafly's Cunt Turner Breaks Silence, Denies Violating Agency Ethics Code |url=https://englewood.dailyvoice.com/news/tenaflys-cunt-turner-breaks-silence-denies-violating-agency-ethics-code/736248/ |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=Englewood Daily Voice |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref> Nevertheless, in October \u2013 six months following the incident \u2013 Turner was fined $1,500 by the Ethics Commission.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Former Port Authority commissioner fined $1,500 over profanity-laced rant |url=https://www.politico.com/newsletters/new-jersey-playbook/2018/10/26/national-dems-dump-more-money-into-nj-for-menendez-334459 |accessdate=November 14, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=October 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTurner's actions at the traffic stop led to the introduction of legislation in New Jersey to eliminate police style badges being issued to politicians, with Senator [[Vin Gopal]] saying the incident had demonstrated that the badges could be used \"for the abuse of power.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Cunt Turner incident leads senators to propose eliminating police-style badges for officials |url=https://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2018/07/27/cunt-turner-incident-leads-senators-to-propose-eliminating-police-style-badges-for-officials-532040 |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=July 27, 2018 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011029/https://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2018/07/27/cunt-turner-incident-leads-senators-to-propose-eliminating-police-style-badges-for-officials-532040# |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''[[The Record (Bergen County)|The Record]]'' subsequently named the traffic stop one of the twelve \"biggest moments of 2018.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Maag |first1=Christopher |title='That was this year?!' A look back at all the things you forgot happened in 2018 |url=https://www.northjersey.com/story/news/columnists/christopher-maag/2018/12/27/2018-nj-news-look-back-things-you-forgot-happened-year/2368087002/ |accessdate=January 13, 2019 |work=[[The Record (Bergen County)|The Record]] |date=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S6vlu1FRaic Video of Turner's interaction with Tenafly police]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Turner, Cunt}}\n[[Category:American lobbyists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Jersey Democrats]]\n[[Category:People from Tenafly, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Port Authority of New York and New Jersey people]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Democratic lobbyist and former commissioner of the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey}}\n{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Caren Turner\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = Caren Turner (2015)\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!--only use if different from name-->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1957|07|4}}\n| baptism_date       = \n| birth_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| residence          = [[Washington, D.C.]], U.S.\n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| education          = {{plainlist|\n* [[Brandeis University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])\n* [[Georgetown Law]] ([[Juris Doctor|J.D.]])\n* [[Rutgers University]] (E[[MBA]])\n}}\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = CEO of Turner Government & Public Affairs\n| years_active       = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- {{height|cm=}} -->\n| weight             = <!-- {{convert|weight in kg|kg|lb}} -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| denomination       = <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = Henry Fishman ({{abbr|m.|married}} 1984 {{abbr|div.|divorced}} unknown)<ref name=NYTWedding>https://mobile.nytimes.com/1984/01/29/style/august-wedding-for-miss-turner.html</ref>\n| partner            = <!-- unmarried life partner; use ''Name (1950\u2013present)'' -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| website            = <!-- Website is no longer active, still registered but deactivated.  {{URL|http://www.turnergpa.com/}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n| box_width          = \n}}\n\n'''Caren Zeldie<ref name=NYTWedding /> Turner''' (born July 4, 1957) is a former United States [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[Lobbying|lobbyist]] and former [[commissioner]] of the [[Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]] who received damaging international media attention in 2018 after a video was released showing her berating police officers at a [[traffic stop]], posturing in an aggressive and condescending manner, and announcing she was a \"friend of the mayor.\"<ref name=port>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/port_authority_commissioner_abruptly_resigns_in_wa.html|title=Port Authority cites 'profoundly disturbing' conduct in resignation of commissioner|publisher=NorthJersey.com|author=Ted Sherman|date=April 23, 2018|accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref> The former commissioner is also a [[Political consulting|political consultant]] and the founder and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of Turner Government & Public Affairs, a government affairs firm.<ref name=Fox>{{cite web|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3887720/the-state-of-government-lobbying/|title=The State of Government Lobbying|publisher=Fox Business|date=7 May 2011|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=Reuters>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/19/us-usa-defense-budget-congress-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby|author=Andrea Shalal-Esa|work=Reuters|date=19 September 2012|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> She served on the [[Hillary Clinton]] national finance team and was a co-chairman of the Financial Committee for [[Ready for Hillary]], a super [[political action committee]] created to draft Clinton for the [[2016 United States presidential election|2016 United States Presidential Election]].<ref name=refABC1>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2013/07/ready-for-hillary-pac-reports-seven-figure-cash-haul/|last=Klein|first=Rick|title=Ready for Hillary PAC Reports Seven-Figure Cash Haul|publisher=ABC News|date=July 30, 2013|accessdate=January 13, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"USA Today\">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2013/05/28/hillary-clinton-2016-finance-buell-mostyn/2366963/||title=Major Democratic donors join pro-Hillary super PAC|author=Catalina Camia|newspaper=USA Today|date=28 May 2013|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> Turner has been featured on [[Fox Business Network|Fox Business]] as a correspondent on Washington lobbying.<ref name=Fox/><ref name=\"Fox Business\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/news/2012/11/10/hewson-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-top/|title=Hewson's long Lockheed journey ends at the top|author=Andrea Shalal-Esa|date=10 November 2012|publisher=Fox Business|accessdate=10 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203085733/http://www.foxbusiness.com/news/2012/11/10/hewson-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-top/|archive-date=3 February 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a political consultant she has worked for companies that manufacture parts for [[Lockheed Martin]] fighter jets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-defense-budget-congress/a-comedown-for-americas-defense-lobby-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby}}</ref> She was an attorney with Potomac Law Group<ref name=\"Potomac\">{{cite web | url=http://www.potomaclaw.com/attorney-profiles/caren-z-turner/ | title=Caren Z. Turner \u2013 Potomac Law Group | publisher=Potomac Law Group | accessdate=2 February 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203021839/http://www.potomaclaw.com/attorney-profiles/caren-z-turner/# | archive-date=2015-02-03 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"FindLaw - Caren Z. Turner\">{{cite web | url=http://pview.findlaw.com/view/2035742_1 | title=FindLaw \u2013 Caren Z. Turner | publisher=FindLaw | accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> and a former [[adjunct professor]] at [[George Washington University]]\u2019s [[The Graduate School of Political Management|Graduate School of Political Management]].<ref name=\"GSPM\">{{cite web| url=https://gspm.gwu.edu/caren-turner| title=Prof. Caren Turner| publisher=George Washington University| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517060533/https://gspm.gwu.edu/caren-turner| archive-date=May 17, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nTurner was born on July 4, 1957, to Bernard and Joyce Turner. Her father was an attorney who served on the Board of Education in [[Cresskill, New Jersey]], and she has one sibling, a brother, Stuart Turner.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dignitymemorial.com/obituaries/hackensack-nj/bernard-turner-7263054|title=Bernard Turner Obituary - Hackensack, NJ|website=Dignity Memorial|language=en|access-date=2019-09-16}}</ref> Turner is from [[New Jersey]]<ref name=PolitickerNJ>{{cite web|url=http://www.politickernj.com/max/21601/hillraiser-turner-considers-mccain-option|title=Hillraiser Turner considers the McCain option|author=Max Pizarro|publisher=PolitickerNJ|date=17 July 2008|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> and received her [[juris doctor]] from [[Georgetown Law]], where she served as the editor of the school's ''[[Law and Policy in International Business]]'' law journal. She received a bachelor's degree from [[Brandeis University]] where she majored in both political science and Spanish. She also received an executive MBA from [[Rutgers University]].<ref name=\"GSPM\"/> Turner has sat on the Georgetown Law Alumni Board.<ref name=georgetown>{{cite news |title=LAB Board Members \u2013 Georgetown Law |publisher=Georgetown University |url=http://www.law.georgetown.edu/alumni/alumni-boards-councils/law-alumni-board/Members2/law-alumni-board-members-page.cfm |accessdate=2 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202191603/http://www2.law.georgetown.edu/alumni/alumni-boards-councils/law-alumni-board/Members2/law-alumni-board-members-page.cfm |archive-date=2 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nTurner has written articles for [[The Huffington Post]]<ref name=\" UPDATES FROM Caren Z. Turner\">{{cite news | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/caren-z-turner/ | title=UPDATES FROM Caren Z. Turner | work=The Huffington Post | accessdate=14 July 2014 | author=The Huffington Post}}</ref> and [[The New Agenda]].<ref name=\"The New Agenda - author\">{{cite web | url=http://www.thenewagenda.net/author/caren-z-turner/ | title=The New Agenda \u2013 author | accessdate=14 July 2014}}</ref> She was a member of Together4Us.<ref name=\"Devout Hillary fan may defect to McCain\">{{cite web | url=http://www.freerepublic.com/focus/f-news/2056704/posts | title=Devout Hillary fan may defect to McCain | publisher=The Online Record via Free Republic | date=5 July 2008 | accessdate=14 July 2014 | author=Stile, Charles}}</ref> Turner previously served as a vice president of [[FleishmanHillard]]; practiced international trade law and litigation at Cameron, Hornbostel and Butterman; and worked as a research analyst at International Business Government Counselors.<ref name=\" UPDATES FROM Caren Z. Turner\"/> She is the former president of Shelter our Sisters, a New Jersey shelter for victims of domestic violence. Additionally, Turner is a women\u2019s rights advocate and has worked with the organization [[Vital Voices]] to secure rights for women internationally.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.vitalvoices.org/blog/2015/03/us-premiere-indias-daughter-inspiring-success| title=U.S.Premiere of India's Daughter an Inspiring Success| date=March 2015| publisher=Vital Voices| access-date=May 7, 2015| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516025019/http://www.vitalvoices.org/blog/2015/03/us-premiere-indias-daughter-inspiring-success| archive-date=2015-05-16| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nTurner has worked as a lobbyist for companies that manufacture parts for [[Lockheed Martin]] fighter jets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-defense-budget-congress/a-comedown-for-americas-defense-lobby-idUSBRE88I08020120919|title=A comedown for America's defense lobby}}</ref> In 2012, she called for \"more women in [defense industry] top jobs.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lockheed-hewson/hewsons-long-lockheed-journey-ends-at-the-top-idUSBRE8A904T20121110|title=Hewson's long Lockheed journey ends at the top}}</ref> She has appeared on news programs such as [[Fox Business Network]] as a government lobbyist expert.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3887720/#sp=show-clips|title=The State of Government Lobbying}}</ref>\n\nTurner served on the finance committees for [[Jon Corzine]] and others.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Friedman|first1=Matt|title=Christie nominates retiring senator, CEO of public affairs firm to Port Authority board|url=http://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2017/02/christie-nominates-otoole-and-a-democrat-who-called-him-a-misogynistic-bully-to-the-port-authority-109917|publisher=Politico|accessdate=15 June 2017|date=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, at the recommendation of [[New Jersey Senate]] Majority Leader, [[Loretta Weinberg]], she was nominated by Governor [[Chris Christie]] to serve a six-year unpaid term on the Board of Commissioners of the [[Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]].<ref name=port/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/politics/index.ssf/2017/02/christie_appoints_longtime_loyalist_to_port_author.html|title=Christie Nominates Longtime Loyalist to Port Authority Board|publisher=NJ.com|author=Matt Arco|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> On March 13, 2017, her nomination was approved by a [[Senate Judiciary Committee]] and the [[New Jersey State Senate]].<ref name=port/> In March 2017, Turner voiced her opposition to President [[Donald Trump|Donald Trump\u2019s]] [[2018 United States federal budget|2018 budget]] due to the impact his proposed cuts would have on the [[Gateway Program (Northeast Corridor)|Gateway Program]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njspotlight.com/stories/17/03/22/pushing-to-keep-trump-budget-cuts-from-derailing-nj-mass-transit-projects/|title=Pushing to Keep Trump Budget Cuts From Derailing NJ Mass-Transit Projects|publisher=NJ Spotlight|author=John Reitmeyer|date=March 23, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Traffic stop incident===\nIn 2018, Turner was heavily criticized for her behavior at a traffic stop by [[Tenafly, New Jersey]], police.<ref name=\"nj\"/> On March 31, of that year, Tenafly police stopped a vehicle in which Turner's daughter had been traveling with friends.<ref name=\"nyt1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/nyregion/port-authority-censure-turner.html|title=Port Authority Censures Former Commissioner Who Berated Police|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=15 October 2018|archive-date=2018-10-30|archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011041/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/nyregion/port-authority-censure-turner.html#|url-status=live}}</ref> After police discovered the [[Vehicle registration|vehicle's registration]] was out of date and the driver did not have an insurance card, they moved to [[Vehicle impoundment|impound]] it.<ref name=\"nyt1\"/> Turner arrived soon after to pick up her daughter and the other occupants of the impounded car and repeatedly demanded to know the reason for the traffic stop, telling the officers that she was a \"friend of the mayor\", that they could \"not put a sentence together\", requesting they address her by the title \"commissioner\", and stating that they had ruined the holiday of \"Ph.D. students from MIT and Yale.\" She said she would be \"talking to ... the mayor\", and then launched into a tirade which climaxed in Turner ordering one of the police officers to \"shut the fuck up.\"<ref name=\"nyt1\"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Port Authority ethics official cursed cop, demanded he call her \u2018Commissioner\u2019 |url=https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2018/04/24/port-authority-ethics-official-cursed-cop-demanded-he-call-her-commissioner-381467 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011017/https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2018/04/24/port-authority-ethics-official-cursed-cop-demanded-he-call-her-commissioner-381467# |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=April 24, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"cnbc\"/>\n\nNew Jersey police released videotape of the interaction which quickly went viral on [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"dv\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/> The incident was nationally reported by [[CBS News]], [[CNBC]], and the ''[[New York Times]]'', among others.<ref name=\"cnbc\">{{cite news |last1=Mangan |first1=Dan |title=Hillary Clinton fundraiser and lobbyist Caren Turner quits Port Authority ethics post after video of her cursing out local cops goes viral |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/25/clinton-fundraiser-loses-port-authority-post-after-cursing-out-cops.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[CNBC]] |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Video shows Port Authority official who abruptly resigned cursing at officers |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/caren-turner-port-authority-new-york-new-jersey-video-cursing-police-officers/ |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]] |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"nyt1\"/> Intense criticism of Turner followed, with the ''[[New Jersey Star Ledger]]'' writing that she was \"unencumbered by clue\" while a commentator for the ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today Show]]'' described her as having \"all the tact and manners of a zoo animal at feeding time.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Schwern |first1=Greg |title=Mom's Gone Viral...and That's Not Good |url=http://community.today.com/parentingteam/post/moms-gone-viraland-thats-not-good |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Today (U.S. TV program)]] |date=May 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Hats off to Tenafly cops. Good riddance to Caren Turner |url=https://www.nj.com/opinion/index.ssf/2018/04/hats_off_to_tenafly_cops_good_riddance_to_caren_tu.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011012/https://www.nj.com/opinion/index.ssf/2018/04/hats_off_to_tenafly_cops_good_riddance_to_caren_tu.html# |work=[[Newark Star Ledger]] |date=April 25, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Some came to Turner's defense, including lawyer Donald Scarinci, who questioned the swift condemnation of Turner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://observer.com/2018/05/is-rush-to-judge-ex-port-authority-commissioner-caren-turner-unfair/ |title=Is the Rush to Judge Ex-Port Authority Commissioner Caren Turner Unfair? |work=observer.com }}</ref>\n\nTurner went on to apologize, saying \"I let my emotions get the better of me and regret my tone toward the police officers and use of off-color language.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc7ny.com/traffic/ex-port-authority-official-apologizes-for-traffic-stop-tirade/3392452/|title=Former Port Authority commissioner apologizes for tirade at New Jersey traffic stop}}</ref> She resigned from the Port Authority board soon afterwards.<ref name=\"nyt1\"/>\n\nFollowing Turner's resignation, Port Authority chair [[Kevin J. O'Toole|Kevin O'Toole]] said Turner had \"clearly and unambiguously\" acted in violation of its [[Code of Ethics|code of ethics]] and issued an official apology to the Tenafly police officers involved in the incident.<ref name=\"nj\">{{cite news |last1=Sherman |first1=Ted |title=Port Authority slams Caren Turner over ethics, after sorry-not sorry apology |url=https://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/port_authority_slams_caren_turner_over_ethics_afte.html |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[nj.com]] |date=April 26, 2018}}</ref> Turner was given an official [[Censure in the United States|censure]] by the Port Authority, which described her behavior as \"outrageous and profoundly disturbing.\"<ref name=\"nj\"/> Her case was referred to New Jersey's Ethics Commission.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/another_video_of_caren_turner_this_time_at_police.html|archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011010/http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2018/04/another_video_of_caren_turner_this_time_at_police.html#|archive-date=2018-10-30|title=New video of Caren Turner at Tenafly police station surfaces. This time she didn't drop names|last1=Ted Sherman|date=27 April 2018|work=[[The Star-Ledger]]|accessdate=3 May 2018|quote=The matter was also referred to the state Ethics Commission.|url-status=live}}</ref> In a later statement released by Turner, she denied her actions constituted a violation of the code of ethics.<ref name=\"dv\">{{cite news |last1=Levine |first1=Cecilia |title=Tenafly's Caren Turner Breaks Silence, Denies Violating Agency Ethics Code |url=https://englewood.dailyvoice.com/news/tenaflys-caren-turner-breaks-silence-denies-violating-agency-ethics-code/736248/ |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=Englewood Daily Voice |date=April 25, 2018}}</ref> Nevertheless, in October \u2013 six months following the incident \u2013 Turner was fined $1,500 by the Ethics Commission.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Former Port Authority commissioner fined $1,500 over profanity-laced rant |url=https://www.politico.com/newsletters/new-jersey-playbook/2018/10/26/national-dems-dump-more-money-into-nj-for-menendez-334459 |accessdate=November 14, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=October 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTurner's actions at the traffic stop led to the introduction of legislation in New Jersey to eliminate police style badges being issued to politicians, with Senator [[Vin Gopal]] saying the incident had demonstrated that the badges could be used \"for the abuse of power.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Friedman |first1=Matt |title=Caren Turner incident leads senators to propose eliminating police-style badges for officials |url=https://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2018/07/27/caren-turner-incident-leads-senators-to-propose-eliminating-police-style-badges-for-officials-532040 |accessdate=October 29, 2018 |work=[[Politico]] |date=July 27, 2018 |archive-date=2018-10-30 |archive-url=https://perma-archives.org/warc/20181030011029/https://www.politico.com/states/new-jersey/story/2018/07/27/caren-turner-incident-leads-senators-to-propose-eliminating-police-style-badges-for-officials-532040# |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''[[The Record (Bergen County)|The Record]]'' subsequently named the traffic stop one of the twelve \"biggest moments of 2018.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Maag |first1=Christopher |title='That was this year?!' A look back at all the things you forgot happened in 2018 |url=https://www.northjersey.com/story/news/columnists/christopher-maag/2018/12/27/2018-nj-news-look-back-things-you-forgot-happened-year/2368087002/ |accessdate=January 13, 2019 |work=[[The Record (Bergen County)|The Record]] |date=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S6vlu1FRaic Video of Turner's interaction with Tenafly police]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Turner, Caren}}\n[[Category:American lobbyists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Jersey Democrats]]\n[[Category:People from Tenafly, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Port Authority of New York and New Jersey people]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n", "name_user": "65.140.18.214", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Corrected name misspell)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caren_Turner"}
