{"title_page": "Herman Geiger-Torel", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n|name        = Herman Geiger-Torel\n|image       = \n|alt         = \n|caption     = \n|birth_date  = {{Birth date|1907|7|13}}\n|birth_place = [[Frankfurt-am-Main]], [[Grand Duchy of Hesse]]\n|death_date  = {{Death date and age|1976|10|6|1907|7|13}}\n|death_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n|other_names = \n|known_for   = \n|occupation  = \n|nationality = \n}}\n'''Herman Geiger-Torel''', {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|OC}} (July 13, 1907 &ndash; October 6, 1976) was a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[opera]] [[Theatre director|director]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Herman Geiger-Torel|encyclopedia=Encyclopedia of Music in Canada|date=16 December 2013|publisher=[[Historica Canada]]|url=https://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/herman-geiger-torel-emc|accessdate=August 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 1969, he was made an Officer of the [[Order of Canada]].<ref>{{OCC|1988}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Archival records|title=Herman Geiger-Torel|inventory_number=CA OTUFM 05|description_URL=https://discoverarchives.library.utoronto.ca/index.php/otufm05-herman-geiger-torel|dates=}}\n* [http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/en/article/herman-geiger-torel-emc Herman Geiger-Torel] at [[Encyclopedia of Music in Canada]]\n* [https://discoverarchives.library.utoronto.ca/index.php/otufm05-herman-geiger-torel Collection of opera scores annotated by Herman Geiger-Torel] at [https://music.library.utoronto.ca/ University of Toronto Music Library]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Geiger-Torel, Herman}}\n[[Category:1907 births]]\n[[Category:1976 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian classical musicians]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to Canada]]\n[[Category:German Jews]]\n[[Category:Canadian Jews]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of German-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian opera directors]]\n[[Category:People from Frankfurt]]\n[[Category:2